special topics in group theory page 1 department colloquium friday january 13 4 15pm bldg 380 room 380 c lexing ying university of texas austin on fast numerical algorithms for electronic structure calculation abstract kohn sham density functional theory ksdft is the most widely used electronic structure theory for condensed matter systems numerical solution of the kohn sham equation has posed many challenging computational questions in this talk we will discuss our recent progress on developing fast numerical methods for solving the kohn sham equations focusing on how to speed up the diagonalization process and how to choose effective basis functions systematically
